name.text: Finding reciprocals of rational and irrational numbers using a calculator

questiontext.text:
Find the reciprocal of the following numbers using a calculator. Leave your answer to 4 decimal places where possible.

a) \(\sqrt{{@number1@}} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]

b) \(\frac{{@number2@}}{ \pi} =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]

c) \({@frac1@} =\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

To find reciprocal of \(\sqrt{{@number1@}}\), \(\frac{{@number2@}}{ \pi} \) and \({@frac1@}\) using a calculator:

  1. Enter the number into the calculator
  2. Press the reciprocal button x^(-1) on the calculator
  3. Press \(=\) sign and read the displayed result.

a) Therefore, the reciprocal of \(\sqrt{{@number1@}}\) is \({@recip_a@} \)

Given to 4 decimal places we have \({@ta1@}\)

b) The reciprocal of \(\frac{{@number2@}}{ \pi} \) is \({@recip_b@} \)
Giving the number to 4 decimal points we have: \({@ta2@}\)

c) Given \({@frac1@}\), the reciprocal is \({@ta3@}\)
